---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '~/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Returns &amp; policy — Soothemade Notes"
  description="The Soothemade Notes returns policy, privacy approach, and licensing terms."
>
  <Nav />
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <div class="eyebrow">— the fine print, plainly —</div>
      <h1>Returns, privacy, and what you can do with your files.</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <article class="legal">
    <h2>Returns</h2>
    <p>Soothemade Notes products are digital downloads — instant PDFs. Because the file is delivered at purchase, we do not offer refunds as a default. If something genuinely doesn't work for you, write to <a href="mailto:notes@soothemade.com">notes@soothemade.com</a> and we'll figure it out. Quietly.</p>

    <h2>Licensing</h2>
    <p>Everything we sell is licensed for personal use. You can print as many copies as you want for yourself and your household, including printing extras to gift to a friend in person. You may not redistribute the PDF file itself, repackage it for sale, or resell printed copies on a marketplace. If you'd like to use a printable in a hospital, doula practice, or clinical setting, write to us — there's a separate license for that.</p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>We collect the absolute minimum. Your email address (only if you subscribe) and your purchase record (only if you buy). We do not run third-party analytics that profile you. We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is cookieless and does not track individuals across sites. We do not share, sell, or rent email addresses — ever. You can unsubscribe with one click from any email we send.</p>

    <h2>The site is not a person</h2>
    <p>Nothing on this site or in our products is medical, mental-health, legal, or financial advice. Some of our products touch sensitive ground (postpartum mental health, c-section recovery) and we are careful with the language — but we are not your provider. If something feels wrong, call yours.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If we materially change this policy, we'll note it on the page with a date. Last revised: May 2026.</p>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: var(--container-narrow);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 64px var(--sp-7) 104px;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 36px 0 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 16px; }
  a { color: var(--accent-soft); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--n-rule-strong); }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .legal { padding: 48px var(--sp-5) 72px; }
  }
</style>
